    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NEWARK AIRPORT CRIME</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Ronald Smothers</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smothers, Ronald</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Port Authority of NY and NJ reports 31.4 percent decline in luggage theft, robbery, pickpocketing and car theft at Newark International Airport during first six months of year (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Newark International Airport may not yet have banished  lost-luggage gremlins, but it has made some progress on human-inspired mischief. According to figures compiled by  Port Authority of New York and New Jersey, crime -- including luggage theft, robbery, pickpocket incidents and car theft -- is down 31.4 percent at the airport for the first six months of this year  in comparison to the same period of 1999.  More modest declines were reported at LaGuardia and Kennedy airports.</p>
        <p>Ronald Smothers</p>
      </block>
